WEBVTT

00:00:00.320 --> 00:00:40.400


00:00:58.139 --> 00:01:01.571
[Episode 1]
[Yumi's Missing Cells]

00:01:15.874 --> 00:01:18.734
Hello, sir.

00:01:18.734 --> 00:01:19.962
What are you doing?

00:01:19.962 --> 00:01:23.636
Looks like you just came from the bathhouse.
Your skin's glowing.

00:01:25.053 --> 00:01:27.986
Man Sik, you got a new car?

00:01:28.720 --> 00:01:29.904
Never seen this one before.

00:01:29.904 --> 00:01:31.431
My daughter bought it for me.

00:01:31.431 --> 00:01:32.849
- Yumi?
- Yeah.

00:01:32.849 --> 00:01:36.979
I told her I didn't need it,
but she bought it anyway.

00:01:36.979 --> 00:01:39.982
Man, I heard Yumi makes serious money.

00:01:39.982 --> 00:01:42.009
So what, one page of writing

00:01:42.009 --> 00:01:44.775
equals the price of this car?

00:01:46.571 --> 00:01:48.865
What? That's what people are saying?

00:01:48.865 --> 00:01:49.950
Yeah.

00:01:49.950 --> 00:01:51.535
It's not that much.

00:01:51.535 --> 00:01:53.620
But yeah, she does pretty well.

00:01:53.620 --> 00:01:55.956
Having a successful daughter, that's the best.

00:01:55.956 --> 00:01:58.292
That's not my money, though.

00:01:58.292 --> 00:01:59.376
Come on.

00:01:59.376 --> 00:02:00.432
Same thing.

00:02:00.432 --> 00:02:01.712
- Oh, right.
- Yeah?

00:02:01.712 --> 00:02:03.796
Did you see the article yesterday?

00:02:03.796 --> 00:02:05.383
No, why?

00:02:05.383 --> 00:02:08.597
Yumi did a newspaper interview.

00:02:08.597 --> 00:02:10.012
[The Queen of Romance,
Author Kim Yumi Interview]

00:02:10.012 --> 00:02:13.223
See? The Queen of Romance,
Author Kim Yumi Interview.

00:02:13.223 --> 00:02:15.726
- She looks great.
- Right?

00:02:15.726 --> 00:02:18.228
[We'll be cheering on your future books too!]
[Keep it up!]

00:02:18.228 --> 00:02:20.022
Hello.

00:02:20.022 --> 00:02:22.357
Hey, Su Jin! What's up?

00:02:22.357 --> 00:02:24.151
- Off to class?
- Yes.

00:02:24.151 --> 00:02:26.528
When's Yumi's new book coming out?

00:02:26.528 --> 00:02:27.863
She's working on it.

00:02:27.863 --> 00:02:30.490
She said that months ago,
but it's been over three months.

00:02:30.490 --> 00:02:32.492
She's probably super busy.

00:02:32.492 --> 00:02:34.536
Lots of interviews and stuff.

00:02:34.536 --> 00:02:35.746
Plus, they're making

00:02:35.746 --> 00:02:37.914
another drama based on her book.

00:02:37.914 --> 00:02:39.750
So there's like a press conference

00:02:39.750 --> 00:02:41.251
she has to attend, too.

00:02:41.251 --> 00:02:43.086
Anyway, it'll be out soon.

00:02:43.086 --> 00:02:45.213
Please ask her when it's starting.

00:02:45.213 --> 00:02:46.340
My whole class is waiting.

00:02:46.340 --> 00:02:48.425
Alright, alright. I'll give her a nudge.

00:02:48.425 --> 00:02:49.868
- Go on.
- Bye.

00:02:49.868 --> 00:02:51.595
Okay, see you.

00:02:51.595 --> 00:02:53.913
Take care.

00:02:55.098 --> 00:02:57.976
Man, seriously...

00:02:57.976 --> 00:03:01.438
They can't even wait a few nights, huh?

00:03:01.438 --> 00:03:04.066
Writers are people too.

00:03:04.066 --> 00:03:06.443
They need a break sometimes.

00:03:06.443 --> 00:03:09.321
Good grief...

00:03:09.321 --> 00:03:11.803
Let's see.

00:03:18.222 --> 00:03:21.091
[Love you, Dad]

00:03:27.513 --> 00:03:28.548
[My daughter]

00:03:28.548 --> 00:03:30.509
Is she busy?

00:03:30.509 --> 00:03:32.803
- Hello?
- Oh! Yumi?

00:03:32.803 --> 00:03:33.970
Dad!

00:03:33.970 --> 00:03:37.916
Hey, where are you? Why can't I hear you?

00:03:37.916 --> 00:03:40.597
Dad, I'm on a plane!

00:03:40.597 --> 00:03:41.730
- A plane?
- Yeah!

00:03:41.730 --> 00:03:43.597
I'm on a plane!

00:03:43.597 --> 00:03:46.097
Why are you on a plane? Where are you going?

00:03:46.097 --> 00:03:48.652
I'm going skydiving.

00:03:48.652 --> 00:03:49.903
What?

00:03:49.903 --> 00:03:51.596
S-k-y-d-i-v-i-n-g.

00:03:51.596 --> 00:03:53.281
"Sky..." What?

00:03:53.281 --> 00:03:56.180
Wait, what about your writing?

00:03:56.180 --> 00:03:58.419
I'm here for research.

00:03:58.419 --> 00:04:00.038
The main character

00:04:00.038 --> 00:04:03.442
falls in love with her instructor
while skydiving.

00:04:03.442 --> 00:04:06.503
That doesn't mean you have to go skydiving!

00:04:06.503 --> 00:04:08.922
We're about to take off. Please hang up.

00:04:08.922 --> 00:04:10.674
- Okay.
- Yes.

00:04:10.674 --> 00:04:13.618
Dad, I'm here with the producer. Don't worry.

00:04:13.618 --> 00:04:17.358
I'll call you later, okay?

00:04:19.470 --> 00:04:21.823
Oh no.

00:05:09.816 --> 00:05:11.180
Writer Kim!

00:05:11.180 --> 00:05:12.252
Yes?

00:05:12.252 --> 00:05:14.597
Do you really have to do this yourself?

00:05:14.597 --> 00:05:16.765
You could totally write
the "falling for your instructor" part

00:05:16.765 --> 00:05:18.709
without actually jumping.

00:05:18.709 --> 00:05:20.577
He's already holding onto you like this...

00:05:20.577 --> 00:05:22.597
See, right?

00:05:22.597 --> 00:05:24.440
- Sorry?
- I mean...

00:05:24.440 --> 00:05:26.211
Just get a feel for it

00:05:26.211 --> 00:05:30.347
and maybe head back down?

00:05:30.347 --> 00:05:32.847
Right now?

00:05:35.876 --> 00:05:38.045
What is it?

00:05:38.045 --> 00:05:40.669
- Oh no.
- Oh my.

00:05:41.839 --> 00:05:43.899
No way!

00:05:43.899 --> 00:05:45.318
Right now!

00:05:45.318 --> 00:05:47.472
How about canceling?

00:05:47.472 --> 00:05:50.674
You're the one who told me to do this!

00:05:50.674 --> 00:05:53.051
You said I'd get the feel if I tried it!

00:05:53.051 --> 00:05:55.186
No, no, I...

00:05:59.632 --> 00:06:01.368
Can we cancel now?

00:06:01.368 --> 00:06:03.328
- I can't do this!
- Let's go!

00:06:03.328 --> 00:06:04.621
- No, no!
- Let's go!

00:06:04.621 --> 00:06:06.856
No, no, seriously, I can't!

00:06:06.856 --> 00:06:08.667
- Please!
- Sir! Sir!

00:06:08.667 --> 00:06:11.314
Wait, wait!

00:06:11.314 --> 00:06:13.508
- Writer Kim, please save me!
- Three, two...

00:06:13.508 --> 00:06:15.448
One!

00:06:17.093 --> 00:06:18.555
- Let's go!
- What?

00:06:18.555 --> 00:06:20.262
Wait, I can't! Hold on!

00:06:20.262 --> 00:06:22.430
Wait, my helmet! Tighten my helmet!

00:06:22.430 --> 00:06:24.266
Wait a second!

00:06:24.266 --> 00:06:26.055
Let's go!

00:06:26.055 --> 00:06:29.638
Ready, set, go!

00:07:09.638 --> 00:07:12.680
What is happening?

00:07:22.555 --> 00:07:25.430
What is this?

00:07:36.720 --> 00:07:38.463
We survived.

00:07:38.463 --> 00:07:39.989
Everyone okay?

00:07:39.989 --> 00:07:41.174
Hey, Writer Cell!

00:07:41.174 --> 00:07:43.092
What the hell was that?

00:07:43.092 --> 00:07:45.303
Do you have to go this extreme to write?

00:07:45.303 --> 00:07:47.830
This was it.

00:07:47.830 --> 00:07:49.974
So this is what it feels like.

00:07:49.974 --> 00:07:51.351
I was wondering

00:07:51.351 --> 00:07:54.401
if you could actually fall in love
while skydiving.

00:07:54.401 --> 00:07:55.438
So?

00:07:55.438 --> 00:07:56.981
Did you get what you needed?

00:07:56.981 --> 00:07:59.680
Can you write it now?

00:07:59.680 --> 00:08:00.718
No.

00:08:00.718 --> 00:08:01.986
What?

00:08:01.986 --> 00:08:05.423
There's no way you'd fall in love
in that kind of chaos.

00:08:05.423 --> 00:08:07.575
[I don't know]
I need a different setup.

00:08:07.575 --> 00:08:09.143
Hey! Just to figure that out,

00:08:09.143 --> 00:08:10.953
Yumi had to risk her life?

00:08:10.953 --> 00:08:14.290
You used to write just fine without this.

00:08:14.290 --> 00:08:15.458
I don't know.

00:08:15.458 --> 00:08:19.362
Now I can't write unless I go this far.

00:08:19.362 --> 00:08:21.572
Beats me.

00:08:37.058 --> 00:08:39.298
Hey!

00:08:40.691 --> 00:08:42.468
Hello!

00:08:42.468 --> 00:08:44.362
- That's so cool.
- Fresh and tasty today...

00:08:44.362 --> 00:08:48.802
- Hi!
- Oh, welcome!

00:08:50.072 --> 00:08:52.036
Dae Yong!

00:08:52.036 --> 00:08:53.704
Dae Yong!

00:08:53.704 --> 00:08:55.729
Come on, hurry!

00:08:55.729 --> 00:08:57.792
- Honey.
- Yeah.

00:08:57.792 --> 00:08:59.013
You've got the car key, right?

00:08:59.013 --> 00:09:01.237
- The key? I don't have it.
- Yes, you do.

00:09:01.237 --> 00:09:02.658
- You used it earlier.
- Did I?

00:09:02.658 --> 00:09:04.938
Oh, here it is. Sorry.

00:09:04.938 --> 00:09:07.165
- I'll open it.
- Let's go.

00:09:07.165 --> 00:09:12.039
- Look at you, so cute.
- Alright, hop in.

00:09:14.439 --> 00:09:16.846
Let's go.

00:09:18.218 --> 00:09:20.131
- You packed everything, huh?
- Yeah.

00:09:21.567 --> 00:09:23.401
Did you cry that much?

00:09:23.401 --> 00:09:25.536
Where do we go first?

00:09:25.536 --> 00:09:26.622
My mom's.

00:09:26.622 --> 00:09:30.340
We drop Ran off there first,
then take me to Yumi's studio.

00:09:30.340 --> 00:09:31.505
Got it.

00:09:31.505 --> 00:09:35.303
And you're stopping by the hospital,
then the publisher, right?

00:09:35.303 --> 00:09:38.225
Okay, perfect.

00:09:38.225 --> 00:09:41.444
Mornings are a battlefield.

00:10:02.598 --> 00:10:04.851
Don't overdo it.

00:10:04.851 --> 00:10:08.204
You mean don't have too much fun?

00:10:11.697 --> 00:10:14.291
- I'll call you.
- Okay.

00:10:18.984 --> 00:10:20.964
Hello.

00:10:31.315 --> 00:10:32.827
Who is it?

00:10:32.827 --> 00:10:35.935
Writer Kim, it's me.

00:10:38.366 --> 00:10:40.217
You're here?

00:10:40.217 --> 00:10:43.446
Oh my.

00:10:43.446 --> 00:10:44.930
Look at you.

00:10:44.930 --> 00:10:49.182
So dedicated to your craft.

00:10:49.182 --> 00:10:51.300
I just made coffee. I'll pour you some.

00:10:51.300 --> 00:10:53.835
Yes, please.

00:10:55.388 --> 00:10:58.059
This is nice.

00:10:58.059 --> 00:10:59.170
Hey.

00:10:59.170 --> 00:11:01.281
I heard Hemingway once said,

00:11:01.281 --> 00:11:02.750
"If you want to write about life,

00:11:02.750 --> 00:11:04.764
you've got to live it first."

00:11:05.513 --> 00:11:07.059
You even know Hemingway?

00:11:07.059 --> 00:11:08.879
Come on.

00:11:08.879 --> 00:11:11.680
I've been married to
a publishing editor for three years.

00:11:11.680 --> 00:11:15.755
The sparrow near a school sings the primer.
You know?

00:11:15.755 --> 00:11:17.200
So...

00:11:17.200 --> 00:11:21.445
you know how Hemingway,
the guy who chased "real life," ended up?

00:11:21.445 --> 00:11:24.641
He shot himself.

00:11:24.641 --> 00:11:26.012
Hey, don't worry.

00:11:26.012 --> 00:11:29.513
I'm no Hemingway. Not even close to that level.

00:11:29.513 --> 00:11:32.441
I just couldn't write, and PD Yoon said,

00:11:32.441 --> 00:11:35.760
"Maybe you'll get a feel for it
if you try skydiving?"

00:11:35.760 --> 00:11:38.388
So I did.

00:11:38.388 --> 00:11:40.305
That PD's the problem.

00:11:40.305 --> 00:11:42.347
Why would they send a writer to do that?

00:11:42.347 --> 00:11:44.803
How's PD Yoon doing?

00:11:44.803 --> 00:11:48.085
Broken toe. That's not healing anytime soon.

00:11:48.085 --> 00:11:49.169
By the way,

00:11:49.169 --> 00:11:51.630
why can't you write?

00:11:51.630 --> 00:11:52.715
I don't know.

00:11:52.715 --> 00:11:55.092
You've already had four hits.

00:11:55.092 --> 00:11:57.678
You're a legit hit writer.

00:11:57.678 --> 00:12:01.807
Just relax and write.
Even if one flops, who cares?

00:12:01.807 --> 00:12:04.753
You're just feeling pressure.

00:12:05.853 --> 00:12:08.547
I don't think it's pressure.

00:12:08.547 --> 00:12:10.816
Then what is it?

00:12:10.816 --> 00:12:13.027
You're not worried about money,

00:12:13.027 --> 00:12:14.987
and you're not tied down with a kid like me.

00:12:14.987 --> 00:12:16.180
You can sleep whenever,

00:12:16.180 --> 00:12:18.949
go wherever you want...

00:12:18.949 --> 00:12:22.311
You've got this amazing studio view,

00:12:22.311 --> 00:12:24.371
fans waiting for your work...

00:12:24.371 --> 00:12:27.064
What's the problem?

00:12:27.916 --> 00:12:30.836
Maybe it's because I have no worries.

00:12:30.836 --> 00:12:32.138
Are you kidding me?

00:12:32.138 --> 00:12:35.090
Sorry, but it kind of feels like that.

00:12:35.090 --> 00:12:37.384
Having no problems...

00:12:37.384 --> 00:12:39.911
is the problem.

00:12:41.764 --> 00:12:44.058
How do I put it...

00:12:44.058 --> 00:12:45.684
Life just feels...

00:12:45.684 --> 00:12:48.535
kind of dull.

00:12:48.535 --> 00:12:50.057
Then go on a trip.

00:12:50.057 --> 00:12:51.482
Like Europe or something.

00:12:51.482 --> 00:12:53.859
I already did that.

00:12:53.859 --> 00:12:55.973
And?

00:12:55.973 --> 00:12:58.739
It was nice.

00:12:58.739 --> 00:13:01.225
"Wow, this is great."

00:13:01.225 --> 00:13:03.077
And that was it.

00:13:03.077 --> 00:13:05.657
Like skydiving.

00:13:32.680 --> 00:13:34.645
I was moved.

00:13:34.645 --> 00:13:36.610
For a moment.

00:13:36.610 --> 00:13:39.603
It was incredible.

00:13:40.615 --> 00:13:43.176
But...

00:13:46.303 --> 00:13:49.128
once that moment passed,

00:13:49.128 --> 00:13:52.464
I just wanted to come down.

00:13:52.464 --> 00:13:54.741
There was no...

00:13:54.741 --> 00:13:57.168
real impact.

00:13:58.046 --> 00:13:59.680
Like your trip?

00:14:00.638 --> 00:14:03.264
Like that.

00:14:03.264 --> 00:14:04.722
Honestly...

00:14:04.722 --> 00:14:06.109
it's because

00:14:06.109 --> 00:14:09.173
you haven't dated in forever.

00:14:09.173 --> 00:14:11.305
- Dating?
- Yeah.

00:14:11.305 --> 00:14:13.840
Hey, you're a romance writer who doesn't date.

00:14:13.840 --> 00:14:16.056
Of course you're stuck.

00:14:16.056 --> 00:14:18.279
You need to start dating.

00:14:18.279 --> 00:14:20.380
You know, Dae Yong said

00:14:20.380 --> 00:14:22.941
there's a whole line of guys
he could set you up with.

00:14:22.941 --> 00:14:25.447
Yeah, but...

00:14:27.094 --> 00:14:28.579
It just feels like a hassle.

00:14:28.579 --> 00:14:33.061
I've seen the guys, they're all great.

00:14:33.061 --> 00:14:34.783
Still, it's a hassle.

00:14:34.783 --> 00:14:36.351
Why though?

00:14:36.351 --> 00:14:38.856
If someone asked me
to go on a blind date right now,

00:14:38.856 --> 00:14:40.347
I'd say yes a hundred times.

00:14:40.347 --> 00:14:41.742
I don't know.

00:14:41.742 --> 00:14:43.394
Everything just feels kind of boring.

00:14:43.394 --> 00:14:45.814
Why?

00:14:46.880 --> 00:14:49.633
Here's why...

00:14:54.853 --> 00:14:58.490
Because a lot of cells
in the village disappeared.

00:15:01.138 --> 00:15:05.763
As the Prime Cell and Writer Cell
grew stronger...

00:15:09.555 --> 00:15:10.786
Little by little,

00:15:10.786 --> 00:15:12.830
cells started vanishing.

00:15:12.830 --> 00:15:15.048
Where'd they go?

00:15:21.472 --> 00:15:23.774
Hey, Emotion Cell.

00:15:23.774 --> 00:15:26.222
Wake up.

00:15:26.222 --> 00:15:27.278
Why?

00:15:27.278 --> 00:15:28.846
Where's Love Cell?

00:15:28.846 --> 00:15:30.205
I can't find it.

00:15:30.205 --> 00:15:32.423
Love Cell?

00:15:37.354 --> 00:15:40.754
Is it gone too?

00:15:44.847 --> 00:15:47.323
Two disappeared just last week

00:15:47.323 --> 00:15:49.616
and now Love Cell's gone too.

00:15:49.616 --> 00:15:52.669
Where is everyone going?

00:15:58.959 --> 00:16:00.513
Actually...

00:16:00.513 --> 00:16:03.763
Love Cell has been really bored lately.

00:16:07.718 --> 00:16:11.757
Every day is so boring.

00:16:16.716 --> 00:16:19.213
Yumi hasn't dated in three years.

00:16:19.213 --> 00:16:20.522
No wonder it's got nothing to do.

00:16:20.522 --> 00:16:23.025
So where did it go?

00:16:23.025 --> 00:16:25.972
Did it run away?

00:16:25.972 --> 00:16:27.905
Love Cell!

00:16:27.905 --> 00:16:29.923
True Heart Cell!

00:16:29.923 --> 00:16:31.575
No-Way Cell!

00:16:31.575 --> 00:16:34.703
- Where are you guys?
- Pride Cell!

00:16:34.703 --> 00:16:38.673
- Love Cell!
- Please, come out!

00:16:43.325 --> 00:16:45.839
Love Cell, True Heart Cell!

00:16:45.839 --> 00:16:48.592
Where are you?

00:16:48.592 --> 00:16:50.959
Careful.

00:16:50.959 --> 00:16:52.763
Love Cell, True Heart Cell.

00:16:52.763 --> 00:16:53.973
Where are you?

00:16:54.972 --> 00:16:57.722
What is that?

00:16:59.605 --> 00:17:01.090
What is it?

00:17:01.090 --> 00:17:02.974
I don't know.

00:17:02.974 --> 00:17:07.087
There's something in our village
even I don't know about.

00:17:54.032 --> 00:17:56.263
What is this? Why is it so cold?

00:17:56.263 --> 00:17:59.388
Is this... a cancer cell base?

00:17:59.388 --> 00:18:03.787
Wait, does Yumi have cancer cells now?

00:18:03.787 --> 00:18:05.860
No.

00:18:06.955 --> 00:18:09.948
That doesn't seem right.

00:18:12.696 --> 00:18:13.921
Love Cell?

00:18:13.921 --> 00:18:16.662
Hey, Love Cell!

00:18:18.972 --> 00:18:21.385
It's a freezer facility.

00:18:21.385 --> 00:18:23.013
What does that mean?

00:18:23.013 --> 00:18:27.289
Cells that aren't needed anymore
get dragged here and frozen.

00:18:42.121 --> 00:18:44.039
It feels flat.

00:18:44.039 --> 00:18:45.791
If I had to sum it up,

00:18:45.791 --> 00:18:47.167
it just feels flat.

00:18:47.167 --> 00:18:48.792
No matter what I see or go through,

00:18:48.792 --> 00:18:50.587
nothing really hits me.

00:18:50.587 --> 00:18:52.323
Nothing really makes me mad.

00:18:52.323 --> 00:18:53.799
Exactly.

00:18:53.799 --> 00:18:55.551
That's why you need to date.

00:18:55.551 --> 00:18:59.054
But here's my problem.

00:18:59.054 --> 00:19:01.097
I actually like it this way.

00:19:01.097 --> 00:19:02.708
- What?
- I don't really have those anymore.

00:19:02.708 --> 00:19:04.727
Getting mad, getting excited, nervous...

00:19:04.727 --> 00:19:08.488
all those emotional ups and downs.

00:19:09.489 --> 00:19:11.648
It's so comfortable.

00:19:11.648 --> 00:19:13.861
Like before,

00:19:13.861 --> 00:19:17.239
when my emotions would go crazy
that kind of thing,

00:19:17.239 --> 00:19:19.180
it just feels like too much now.

00:19:19.180 --> 00:19:20.242
Hey.

00:19:20.242 --> 00:19:22.036
You've got a serious problem.

00:19:22.036 --> 00:19:23.513
Your body's in your 30s,

00:19:23.513 --> 00:19:25.706
but your heart's 80.

00:19:25.706 --> 00:19:27.708
That might be true.

00:19:27.708 --> 00:19:29.376
Wait, that's it.

00:19:29.376 --> 00:19:31.211
You're totally dried-up.

00:19:31.211 --> 00:19:33.104
Maybe I am.

00:19:38.380 --> 00:19:41.347
You've just got it too easy.

00:19:41.347 --> 00:19:44.388
I'm seriously jealous of you.

00:19:44.388 --> 00:19:45.434
Hey,

00:19:45.434 --> 00:19:48.604
when do I get to stop worrying about money
and raising a kid?

00:19:48.604 --> 00:19:51.750
About 19 more years?

00:19:51.750 --> 00:19:55.116
- 19 years.
- Oh my...

00:19:55.116 --> 00:19:56.695
I've got to go.

00:19:56.695 --> 00:19:58.238
- Okay.
- Going down.

00:19:58.238 --> 00:19:59.264
First floor.

00:19:59.264 --> 00:20:04.490
I wish I could feel that "flat" life
just for one day.

00:20:04.490 --> 00:20:05.704
Take care.

00:20:05.704 --> 00:20:08.043
I'll call you.

00:20:17.490 --> 00:20:18.763
Yes, Editor.

00:20:18.763 --> 00:20:20.619
I Da just left.

00:20:20.619 --> 00:20:22.537
Oh, okay.

00:20:22.537 --> 00:20:24.347
How's PD Yoon doing?

00:20:24.347 --> 00:20:27.309
I'm dying over here.

00:20:27.309 --> 00:20:29.412
Ms. Seulgi, hold on a second.

00:20:29.412 --> 00:20:31.249
Yes.

00:20:31.980 --> 00:20:34.400
- That silly guy?
- Are you okay?

00:20:34.400 --> 00:20:36.285
He's got a cast on, so he'll be better.

00:20:36.285 --> 00:20:39.071
But it'll take about a month.

00:20:39.071 --> 00:20:40.594
I hope he gets better soon.

00:20:40.594 --> 00:20:43.308
You know, I told him to help you,

00:20:43.308 --> 00:20:46.803
not jump out of a plane with you. That's silly.

00:20:46.803 --> 00:20:48.622
Oh, hey.

00:20:48.622 --> 00:20:49.895
Thanks.

00:20:49.895 --> 00:20:51.692
So I told her...

00:20:51.692 --> 00:20:52.937
"Writer Kim,

00:20:52.937 --> 00:20:54.513
I'll go first."

00:20:54.513 --> 00:20:59.602
Then I jumped,
and right behind me, she was screaming.

00:20:59.602 --> 00:21:01.013
Anyway,

00:21:01.013 --> 00:21:04.284
I definitely got the full skydiving experience.

00:21:04.284 --> 00:21:05.789
Well...

00:21:05.789 --> 00:21:08.976
PD Yoon will need some time off,

00:21:08.976 --> 00:21:12.888
so we're assigning a new PD for you.

00:21:12.888 --> 00:21:16.013
Someone very calm and rational.

00:21:16.013 --> 00:21:17.638
Oh, okay.

00:21:17.638 --> 00:21:21.071
He's new, but extremely calm and level-headed.

00:21:21.071 --> 00:21:25.630
Honestly, you won't find anyone more composed.

00:21:25.630 --> 00:21:26.869
Well...

00:21:26.869 --> 00:21:29.207
he doesn't have to be that calm though...

00:21:29.207 --> 00:21:31.947
Anyway, got it.

00:21:31.947 --> 00:21:34.208
Okay.

00:21:44.418 --> 00:21:46.720
Now I get it.

00:21:48.038 --> 00:21:49.231
The ones who disappeared

00:21:49.231 --> 00:21:52.450
they were all tied to emotions.

00:21:55.439 --> 00:21:56.632
Love Cell.

00:21:56.632 --> 00:21:59.017
I didn't expect to find you here.

00:21:59.017 --> 00:22:02.477
You were incredible.

00:22:04.138 --> 00:22:05.430
Guys!

00:22:05.430 --> 00:22:07.555
The day is finally here!

00:22:07.555 --> 00:22:09.263
Go get True Heart Cell.

00:22:11.801 --> 00:22:15.608
- Hooray! Go Yumi!
- Guys, I'm getting dizzy.

00:22:18.101 --> 00:22:19.551
Naughty Cell...

00:22:19.551 --> 00:22:21.542
You fell asleep too.

00:22:21.542 --> 00:22:25.159
No chance for Yumi to feel that way lately.

00:22:27.347 --> 00:22:28.805
Let it all loose!

00:22:28.805 --> 00:22:33.084
All Yumi needs is a bed!

00:22:33.084 --> 00:22:34.495
Yes!

00:22:34.495 --> 00:22:36.883
Kiss!

00:22:39.701 --> 00:22:41.794
Tongue Cell, you too.

00:22:41.794 --> 00:22:43.812
You used to be on fire.

00:22:43.812 --> 00:22:46.845
Nice to meet you. I'm Yumi's tongue.

00:22:46.845 --> 00:22:49.516
We used to listen to music

00:22:49.516 --> 00:22:52.062
and dance together.

00:22:53.088 --> 00:22:54.754
Yeah.

00:22:54.754 --> 00:22:56.473
Now that Yumi's life is stable,

00:22:56.473 --> 00:22:59.150
even Hysteria is gone.

00:23:00.375 --> 00:23:02.223
Hysterical Cell!

00:23:02.223 --> 00:23:04.946
All that stuff we held in,

00:23:04.946 --> 00:23:06.886
let's blow it all up, Yumi!

00:23:06.886 --> 00:23:10.479
Burn it all down!

00:23:12.069 --> 00:23:14.665
- Everyone!
- Run!

00:23:14.665 --> 00:23:17.430
Yumi hates this kind of thing.

00:23:17.430 --> 00:23:20.638
It's too much for her. No way, no way.

00:23:20.638 --> 00:23:21.763
Right now...

00:23:21.763 --> 00:23:26.231
Yumi doesn't really hate anything,
but she doesn't really love anything either.

00:23:26.231 --> 00:23:28.423
- ♪ Call out to me ♪
- ♪ Call out to me ♪

00:23:28.423 --> 00:23:31.034
- ♪ Let it out loud ♪
- ♪ Let it out loud ♪

00:23:31.034 --> 00:23:34.180
♪ Through the pain and sorrow... ♪

00:23:39.243 --> 00:23:42.755
Five o'clock!
Target spotted, totally Yumi's type!

00:23:46.737 --> 00:23:49.263
She doesn't even look for someone
to date anymore,

00:23:49.263 --> 00:23:51.972
or even guard against it.

00:23:53.366 --> 00:23:56.138
- I might end up here soon too.
- What?

00:23:56.138 --> 00:23:59.863
I've got nothing to do these days,
and I keep getting sleepy.

00:23:59.863 --> 00:24:02.061
Before Love Cell disappeared,

00:24:02.061 --> 00:24:04.097
it kept saying it was tired too.

00:24:04.097 --> 00:24:06.638
No!

00:24:08.763 --> 00:24:12.117
If you fall asleep too,
what am I supposed to do?

00:24:12.117 --> 00:24:15.183
But I'm sleepy.

00:24:18.052 --> 00:24:20.638
Emotion Cell!

00:24:23.816 --> 00:24:26.770
How do we wake them up?

00:24:26.770 --> 00:24:30.675
Wouldn't they wake up if Yumi feels more?

00:24:30.675 --> 00:24:34.317
Is that even possible?

00:24:34.317 --> 00:24:37.984
Even jumping out of a plane didn't work.

00:24:42.132 --> 00:24:43.284
And now,

00:24:43.284 --> 00:24:47.910
a super calm, hyper-rational PD is coming?

00:25:00.663 --> 00:25:04.983
Then Yumi's just going to get even more numb.

00:25:08.615 --> 00:25:11.075
I'm coming.

00:25:15.572 --> 00:25:17.680
Hello.

00:25:17.680 --> 00:25:18.890
Hello.

00:25:18.890 --> 00:25:21.100
Nice to meet you.

00:25:21.100 --> 00:25:23.920
I'm Yumi's assistant writer, Baek Na Hui.

00:25:23.920 --> 00:25:26.154
Welcome. Please come in.

00:25:26.154 --> 00:25:29.687
Writer Kim! The PD's here!

00:25:30.985 --> 00:25:32.904
- Oh, he's here?
- You know what?

00:25:32.904 --> 00:25:33.933
The new PD.

00:25:33.933 --> 00:25:37.421
He is super young, super tall, super handsome.

00:25:37.421 --> 00:25:39.474
Oh my.

00:25:47.112 --> 00:25:48.472
Hello.

00:25:48.472 --> 00:25:50.213
Hello.

00:25:50.213 --> 00:25:51.714
Nice to meet you.

00:25:51.714 --> 00:25:54.072
I'm Kim Yumi.

00:25:54.072 --> 00:25:56.928
I'm assistant writer Baek Na Hui.

00:25:56.928 --> 00:25:59.555
Yes, I was told earlier.

00:25:59.555 --> 00:26:00.598
Come in.

00:26:00.598 --> 00:26:01.724
Thank you.

00:26:01.724 --> 00:26:03.017
Dae Yong was right.

00:26:03.017 --> 00:26:06.224
He literally looks like
"calm" is written on his face.

00:26:07.780 --> 00:26:09.982
With this ultra-calm PD,

00:26:09.982 --> 00:26:13.868
will even more cells disappear?

00:26:13.868 --> 00:26:15.313
[Producer Shin Soon Rok]

00:26:15.313 --> 00:26:18.111
PD Shin Soon Rok.

00:26:18.111 --> 00:26:20.785
Yeah, I look forward to working with you.

00:26:20.785 --> 00:26:23.055
That's a unique name.

00:26:23.055 --> 00:26:24.117
Yes.

00:26:24.117 --> 00:26:28.297
I bet people called you Rudolph in school.

00:26:31.712 --> 00:26:33.922
They did.

00:26:33.922 --> 00:26:36.268
Or maybe...

00:26:44.513 --> 00:26:47.013
[Strawberry Cream Custard Bungeoppang]

00:26:47.013 --> 00:26:49.307
[Episode 2]

00:26:51.607 --> 00:26:54.234
I'll head out first.

00:26:54.234 --> 00:26:55.944
Good job. See you next week.

00:26:55.944 --> 00:26:56.987
See you.

00:26:56.987 --> 00:26:59.640
Okay, bye.

00:27:02.785 --> 00:27:06.939
Handsome, handsome, we got a handsome PD.

00:27:06.939 --> 00:27:11.210
This is going to make work way more fun.

00:27:11.210 --> 00:27:15.005
The writing's just going to flow now.

00:27:15.005 --> 00:27:18.665
Once Na Hui, the chatty extrovert, left...

00:27:20.554 --> 00:27:21.972
Suddenly,

00:27:21.972 --> 00:27:25.180
everything went quiet.

00:27:43.472 --> 00:27:46.663
My assistant writer...

00:27:46.663 --> 00:27:48.763
She's very upbeat.

00:27:48.763 --> 00:27:50.513
A little scattered,

00:27:50.513 --> 00:27:53.164
but fun to be around.

00:27:53.164 --> 00:27:55.210
Yeah.

00:27:55.869 --> 00:27:58.137
Right?

00:27:59.997 --> 00:28:03.315
Would you like to review the contract?

00:28:03.315 --> 00:28:05.160
Oh, sure.

00:28:05.160 --> 00:28:07.305
I've already looked it over,

00:28:07.305 --> 00:28:11.369
and I'll point out anything
you should pay close attention to.

00:28:11.369 --> 00:28:13.338
Okay.

00:28:19.055 --> 00:28:20.706
[Producer Shin Soon Rok]

00:28:22.905 --> 00:28:24.336
By the way,

00:28:24.336 --> 00:28:27.549
have we met before?

00:28:28.309 --> 00:28:31.248
Your name sounds familiar.

00:28:31.248 --> 00:28:32.847
How long have you been with...

00:28:32.847 --> 00:28:34.610
About a year.

00:28:34.610 --> 00:28:38.388
Oh, really?

00:28:38.388 --> 00:28:39.929
But I feel like we met...

00:28:39.929 --> 00:28:43.562
I did introduce myself once,
when I was assigned to you.

00:28:43.562 --> 00:28:44.638
Right?

00:28:44.638 --> 00:28:46.513
Yeah, that's right.

00:28:46.513 --> 00:28:48.718
About three years ago, huh?

00:28:48.718 --> 00:28:50.055
Yes.

00:28:50.055 --> 00:28:51.097
Oh, but then...

00:28:51.097 --> 00:28:54.146
I left the company shortly after.

00:28:54.146 --> 00:28:57.284
You're that PD Shin from back then.

00:28:57.284 --> 00:29:00.687
We were supposed to meet,
but I heard you'd left.

00:29:00.687 --> 00:29:04.565
So you worked somewhere else
and then came back?

00:29:04.565 --> 00:29:05.763
Yes.

00:29:05.763 --> 00:29:08.532
And now you're assigned to me again.

00:29:08.532 --> 00:29:12.140
I guess we're meant to be connected.

00:29:20.054 --> 00:29:21.772
Here.

00:29:21.772 --> 00:29:23.972
Okay.

00:29:30.972 --> 00:29:33.757
They said he's the calmest person ever,

00:29:33.757 --> 00:29:35.737
but this is too calm.

00:29:35.737 --> 00:29:38.575
Why doesn't he react to anything?

00:29:38.575 --> 00:29:40.426
This is so boring.

00:29:40.426 --> 00:29:42.776
I'm going to sleep.

00:29:42.776 --> 00:29:46.795
Emotion Cell, you're sleeping again?

00:30:01.996 --> 00:30:04.421
Everything looks fine.

00:30:04.421 --> 00:30:07.139
Okay, then could you sign here?

00:30:07.139 --> 00:30:08.177
Sure.

00:30:08.177 --> 00:30:11.843
Just sign on the last page.

00:30:22.607 --> 00:30:25.454
Thank you.

00:30:26.918 --> 00:30:28.513
Would you like something else to drink?

00:30:28.513 --> 00:30:31.867
No, I'm good.

00:30:31.867 --> 00:30:34.222
Oh, I actually have some chocolate
I got as a gift...

00:30:34.222 --> 00:30:37.559
I should get going.

00:30:37.559 --> 00:30:39.007
Oh, okay.

00:30:39.007 --> 00:30:42.796
- Thank you for the coffee.
- My pleasure.

00:30:55.881 --> 00:30:58.972
Did you drive here?
If you need parking validation...

00:30:58.972 --> 00:31:00.805
No, I took the bus.

00:31:00.805 --> 00:31:02.480
I see.

00:31:02.480 --> 00:31:05.149
You said you live in Ilsan, right? Madu-dong?

00:31:05.149 --> 00:31:06.192
Yes.

00:31:06.192 --> 00:31:09.070
Oh, we live in the same neighborhood.

00:31:09.070 --> 00:31:12.050
- You take the 545, right?
- Yes.

00:31:12.050 --> 00:31:13.825
Oh, I knew it.

00:31:13.825 --> 00:31:15.577
Then I'll see you next week.

00:31:15.577 --> 00:31:17.704
Okay, have a good weekend.

00:31:17.704 --> 00:31:20.644
- See you.
- Okay, bye.

00:31:24.728 --> 00:31:27.005
I'll get going then.

00:31:27.005 --> 00:31:29.278
Bye.

00:31:40.518 --> 00:31:43.521
He barely talks.

00:31:43.521 --> 00:31:46.566
Like, seriously short answers.

00:31:46.566 --> 00:31:50.737
Well... I guess that's better than
someone who talks too much.

00:31:50.737 --> 00:31:53.549
Short is better than long.

00:31:53.549 --> 00:31:56.656
He said he's taking the bus...

00:31:56.656 --> 00:31:58.244
Let's wait ten minutes

00:31:58.244 --> 00:32:01.429
so we don't run into him.

00:32:07.921 --> 00:32:10.641
Ten minutes, right?

00:32:53.606 --> 00:32:55.557
You're still here?

00:32:55.557 --> 00:32:57.637
I thought you left a while ago.

00:32:57.637 --> 00:32:58.680
I did.

00:32:58.680 --> 00:33:02.100
- I was on a call.
- Oh, okay.

00:33:03.059 --> 00:33:05.410
You take the 545, right?

00:33:05.410 --> 00:33:06.597
Yes.

00:33:06.597 --> 00:33:07.729
You too, right?

00:33:07.729 --> 00:33:10.823
- Oh, yeah.
- I see.

00:33:13.687 --> 00:33:15.487
Same bus...

00:33:15.487 --> 00:33:17.520
Yeah.

00:33:20.659 --> 00:33:22.811
This is so awkward.

00:33:22.811 --> 00:33:26.507
I should've said I'm taking a different bus.

00:33:26.507 --> 00:33:27.931
Let's put the earbuds back in.

00:33:27.931 --> 00:33:29.597
Listening to music would feel more natural...

00:33:29.597 --> 00:33:33.094
Absolutely not!

00:33:34.890 --> 00:33:35.972
Manners Cell, come on.

00:33:35.972 --> 00:33:37.659
The conversation keeps dying.

00:33:37.659 --> 00:33:39.094
He only gives short answers.

00:33:39.094 --> 00:33:40.162
No way.

00:33:40.162 --> 00:33:43.015
You cannot put in earbuds
when you're with someone.

00:33:43.015 --> 00:33:45.795
That is extremely rude.

00:33:45.795 --> 00:33:49.761
Okay, fair point.

00:34:12.998 --> 00:34:14.713
Oh, there it is.

00:34:14.713 --> 00:34:17.266
Our bus is here.

00:34:31.063 --> 00:34:33.840
How long have you lived around here?

00:34:33.840 --> 00:34:35.265
As for me,

00:34:35.265 --> 00:34:37.110
it's been over seven years.

00:34:37.110 --> 00:34:38.512
About three months.

00:34:38.512 --> 00:34:40.347
Oh, not long then.

00:34:40.347 --> 00:34:41.406
Right.

00:34:41.406 --> 00:34:42.638
What made you move?

00:34:42.638 --> 00:34:44.513
Closer to the publishing company?

00:34:44.513 --> 00:34:45.577
Yes.

00:34:45.577 --> 00:34:50.049
Oh, because it's close.

00:34:50.049 --> 00:34:52.143
Yes.

00:34:54.013 --> 00:34:55.161
As for me,

00:34:55.161 --> 00:34:57.024
I moved here back when
I was at a noodle company.

00:34:57.024 --> 00:34:59.472
The rent was cheap, so I picked this place.

00:34:59.472 --> 00:35:02.803
Then I became a writer
and realized the publisher's nearby.

00:35:02.803 --> 00:35:07.597
I never thought I'd end up a writer back then.

00:35:07.597 --> 00:35:10.347
Oh, I see.

00:35:16.138 --> 00:35:20.195
You don't talk much, do you?

00:35:20.195 --> 00:35:22.739
Not really.

00:35:29.305 --> 00:35:33.537
Being "calm" can be exhausting in its own way.

00:35:33.537 --> 00:35:36.013
This PD has a problem too.

00:35:36.013 --> 00:35:38.463
Talking too little is also rude.

00:35:38.463 --> 00:35:41.180
See? Wearing earbuds would've been better.

00:35:41.180 --> 00:35:43.638
I said that's rude!

00:35:43.638 --> 00:35:45.638
Listening to music when you're with someone?

00:35:45.638 --> 00:35:49.597
How could you be so impolite!

00:36:11.454 --> 00:36:13.860
No way!

00:36:23.421 --> 00:36:26.706
I can't sleep now, seriously!

00:36:26.706 --> 00:36:27.763
Did you see that?

00:36:27.763 --> 00:36:30.888
What was that?
Earbuds while walking with someone?

00:36:30.888 --> 00:36:32.430
When did you wake up?

00:36:32.430 --> 00:36:34.711
Seriously, what is his deal?

00:36:34.711 --> 00:36:37.891
That's just bad manners.

00:36:37.891 --> 00:36:43.081
Maybe he's just not much of a talker,
so he's awkward too, huh?

00:36:43.081 --> 00:36:46.008
Still, that's not okay.

00:36:48.063 --> 00:36:50.176
Beats me.

00:37:15.263 --> 00:37:18.958
No. I can't keep walking with him like this.

00:37:18.958 --> 00:37:20.323
Okay.

00:37:20.323 --> 00:37:22.634
First, ask which way he's going,

00:37:22.634 --> 00:37:24.856
then we go the opposite way.

00:37:27.571 --> 00:37:29.014
- Well...
- Which way...

00:37:29.014 --> 00:37:31.474
are you headed?

00:37:31.474 --> 00:37:32.825
Me?

00:37:32.825 --> 00:37:34.438
Yes.

00:37:34.438 --> 00:37:36.519
What? He beat us to it.

00:37:36.519 --> 00:37:38.892
What do we do?

00:37:42.401 --> 00:37:44.653
Which way

00:37:44.653 --> 00:37:48.158
do you think I'm going?

00:37:48.158 --> 00:37:51.004
- Sorry?
- Want to guess?

00:37:55.805 --> 00:37:58.388
Just kidding.

00:38:00.817 --> 00:38:02.323
Which way are you going?

00:38:02.323 --> 00:38:03.356
This way...

00:38:03.356 --> 00:38:05.180
Oh, then we're going opposite directions.

00:38:05.180 --> 00:38:06.943
I'm going that way.

00:38:06.943 --> 00:38:09.153
Oh, okay.

00:38:09.153 --> 00:38:11.353
- Alright then...
- Bye.

00:38:11.353 --> 00:38:13.899
Bye.

00:38:20.335 --> 00:38:22.458
That was exhausting.

00:38:22.458 --> 00:38:25.152
Weirdly exhausting.

00:38:36.477 --> 00:38:37.807
Hello?

00:38:37.807 --> 00:38:38.849
Hey, Na Hui.

00:38:38.849 --> 00:38:42.263
Our next meeting is at six, right?

00:38:42.263 --> 00:38:43.312
Yes.

00:38:43.312 --> 00:38:45.773
Can you get there by 5:50?

00:38:45.773 --> 00:38:47.108
Yes, of course.

00:38:47.108 --> 00:38:48.192
But why?

00:38:48.192 --> 00:38:50.236
I think PD Shin might get there early.

00:38:50.236 --> 00:38:53.239
- Huh?
- It's kind of awkward talking to him.

00:38:53.239 --> 00:38:54.657
I need you there.

00:38:54.657 --> 00:38:58.077
I know. He is pretty quiet.

00:38:58.077 --> 00:38:59.870
I don't mind, though.

00:38:59.870 --> 00:39:01.480
Exactly, that's why I need you.

00:39:01.480 --> 00:39:04.125
- Don't be late. Okay?
- Got it.

00:39:04.125 --> 00:39:06.876
Okay, see you next week.

00:39:08.421 --> 00:39:10.298
That drained me.

00:39:10.298 --> 00:39:14.238
I didn't even do anything, and I'm exhausted.

00:39:15.344 --> 00:39:16.887
You tired?

00:39:16.887 --> 00:39:18.222
If you're tired,

00:39:18.222 --> 00:39:22.018
let's get Strawberry Cream Custard Bungeoppang.

00:39:22.018 --> 00:39:25.504
When your blood sugar drops, that's the answer.

00:39:25.504 --> 00:39:27.589
Let's go.

00:39:55.888 --> 00:39:59.430
What? That's PD Shin.

00:39:59.430 --> 00:40:02.323
He's not home yet?

00:40:03.017 --> 00:40:05.638
Don't say hi. It'll get awkward again.

00:40:05.638 --> 00:40:07.957
Let's just keep it low-key.

00:40:19.283 --> 00:40:21.849
Guess he's heading somewhere.

00:40:33.839 --> 00:40:35.644
Same direction.

00:40:35.644 --> 00:40:37.138
[Long way around]
Should we go another way?

00:40:37.138 --> 00:40:38.302
No!

00:40:38.302 --> 00:40:40.096
[Adds 7 minutes. Store will close]
If we want to make it before closing,

00:40:40.096 --> 00:40:42.436
[Fastest route]
we have to go this way.

00:40:53.359 --> 00:40:56.141
- Hello.
- Hello.

00:40:56.141 --> 00:40:57.446
What?

00:40:57.446 --> 00:41:00.055
Is he getting bungeoppang too?

00:41:00.055 --> 00:41:02.363
I thought this was my hidden spot.

00:41:02.363 --> 00:41:03.853
Guess it got popular.

00:41:03.853 --> 00:41:07.528
He'll probably just get Red Bean Bungeoppang.

00:41:07.528 --> 00:41:09.680
The real hidden gem is

00:41:09.680 --> 00:41:13.138
the Strawberry Cream Custard Bungeoppang.

00:41:16.707 --> 00:41:20.374
Ten Strawberry Cream Custard Bungeoppang,
please.

00:41:23.722 --> 00:41:24.825
Sorry, but

00:41:24.825 --> 00:41:27.309
we're out of
Strawberry Cream Custard Bungeoppang.

00:41:27.309 --> 00:41:30.229
These eight are all we have left.

00:41:30.229 --> 00:41:31.896
Then I'll take all of them.

00:41:31.896 --> 00:41:33.362
Sure.

00:41:33.362 --> 00:41:36.418
He bought them all?

00:41:36.418 --> 00:41:38.361
Why eight?

00:41:38.361 --> 00:41:40.525
Isn't three or four enough?

00:41:40.525 --> 00:41:42.406
What about me?

00:41:42.406 --> 00:41:45.993
What is happening?

00:41:45.993 --> 00:41:49.453
Hi, again.

00:41:49.453 --> 00:41:52.754
I saw you from behind.

00:41:52.754 --> 00:41:54.938
Oh, Writer Kim.

00:41:55.753 --> 00:41:58.923
I didn't know you knew this place.

00:41:58.923 --> 00:42:01.250
I thought it was my little secret.

00:42:02.569 --> 00:42:03.970
It's really good.

00:42:03.970 --> 00:42:05.221
Right?

00:42:05.221 --> 00:42:07.406
I've been coming here for years.

00:42:08.349 --> 00:42:09.809
Especially,

00:42:09.809 --> 00:42:12.561
the Strawberry Cream Custard Bungeoppang.

00:42:12.561 --> 00:42:14.063
That's all I get.

00:42:14.063 --> 00:42:16.357
I see.

00:42:16.357 --> 00:42:18.818
Here you go.

00:42:18.818 --> 00:42:21.297
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

00:42:24.054 --> 00:42:25.199
Okay, done.

00:42:25.199 --> 00:42:28.220
- Thank you.
- All right.

00:42:28.220 --> 00:42:30.371
Then...

00:42:30.371 --> 00:42:32.297
Bye.

00:42:36.210 --> 00:42:38.404
That's not just being brief.

00:42:38.404 --> 00:42:41.048
That's ignoring her.

00:42:41.048 --> 00:42:43.909
My bungeoppang, my bungeoppang!

00:42:43.909 --> 00:42:45.344
No manners at all.

00:42:45.344 --> 00:42:46.912
Seriously, none.

00:42:46.912 --> 00:42:49.140
- Give me my bungeoppang!
- He's not just quiet.

00:42:49.140 --> 00:42:51.976
- He's a jerk.
- My Strawberry Cream Custard Bungeoppang...

00:42:51.976 --> 00:42:53.936
Maybe he didn't hear Yumi.

00:42:53.936 --> 00:42:56.647
He probably missed it.

00:42:56.647 --> 00:42:59.100
Excuse me.

00:43:01.277 --> 00:43:05.114
They're sold out. Right?

00:43:05.114 --> 00:43:06.907
What?

00:43:06.907 --> 00:43:09.785
The Strawberry Cream Custard Bungeoppang.

00:43:09.785 --> 00:43:13.164
I came for those too.

00:43:13.164 --> 00:43:15.642
That was the last batch.

00:43:17.393 --> 00:43:18.919
No way...

00:43:18.919 --> 00:43:20.910
Even after all that hinting...

00:43:20.910 --> 00:43:23.132
They sell out fast.

00:43:23.132 --> 00:43:24.675
Right.

00:43:24.675 --> 00:43:26.886
So...

00:43:26.886 --> 00:43:28.095
No way...

00:43:28.095 --> 00:43:30.681
Even with a hint that obvious?

00:43:30.681 --> 00:43:32.016
Anyway, I'll get going.

00:43:32.016 --> 00:43:34.474
See you next week.

00:43:42.344 --> 00:43:44.111
He just ignored me?

00:43:44.111 --> 00:43:45.946
My bungeoppang...

00:43:45.946 --> 00:43:48.790
He's a tough one.

00:43:49.842 --> 00:43:54.506
The day she lost all eight
Strawberry Cream Custard Bungeoppang,

00:43:54.506 --> 00:43:56.624
one dormant cell

00:43:56.624 --> 00:43:58.970
woke up.

00:44:28.911 --> 00:44:31.235
I hate

00:44:31.235 --> 00:44:33.160
Shin Soon Rok.

00:44:33.160 --> 00:44:38.205
I really hate him!

00:44:38.205 --> 00:44:42.492
[Episode 3]
[On the Intelligence of Maltese Dogs]

00:44:43.878 --> 00:44:47.606
The only gate into Yumi's Village.

00:44:47.606 --> 00:44:48.805
As you all know,

00:44:48.805 --> 00:44:52.337
getting into Yumi's heart is not easy.

00:44:52.337 --> 00:44:55.358
- Yeah, not easy.
- Not easy.

00:44:55.358 --> 00:44:56.557
The password

00:44:56.557 --> 00:44:58.643
is super long and complicated.

00:44:58.643 --> 00:45:01.548
But that doesn't mean no one can get in.

00:45:01.548 --> 00:45:02.730
Right.

00:45:02.730 --> 00:45:05.675
Cute ones can get in without a password.

00:45:05.675 --> 00:45:08.343
For example...

00:45:09.461 --> 00:45:11.280
Like that frog a long time ago.

00:45:21.292 --> 00:45:23.951
And today...

00:45:26.754 --> 00:45:28.047
Oh my gosh.

00:45:28.047 --> 00:45:30.441
Hi, I'm here.

00:45:30.441 --> 00:45:32.134
If you don't like dogs...

00:45:32.134 --> 00:45:33.594
No, not at all.

00:45:33.594 --> 00:45:35.927
Come in, come in.

00:45:36.889 --> 00:45:39.041
Oh my gosh.

00:45:39.041 --> 00:45:41.634
Come here, come here.

00:45:46.317 --> 00:45:48.018
[Open the door]

00:45:49.026 --> 00:45:52.278
- Got it. 3-7-2-8-2-0...
- Got it.

00:45:52.278 --> 00:45:54.245
You know...

00:45:55.574 --> 00:45:58.573
- A Maltese. So cute.
- Oh my.

00:46:03.499 --> 00:46:06.502
A Maltese has entered Yumi's heart.

00:46:06.502 --> 00:46:09.380
Hi, I'm Yumi.

00:46:09.380 --> 00:46:11.716
What's your name?

00:46:11.716 --> 00:46:14.405
"My name is Coco."

00:46:14.405 --> 00:46:15.928
Coco.

00:46:15.928 --> 00:46:17.112
Nice to meet you.

00:46:17.112 --> 00:46:18.472
Isn't she cute?

00:46:18.472 --> 00:46:20.933
She's even prettier in person.

00:46:20.933 --> 00:46:22.752
So cute.

00:46:22.752 --> 00:46:25.672
She really is.

00:46:26.397 --> 00:46:29.323
Hold on.

00:46:29.323 --> 00:46:32.361
Coco, your fur is so soft.

00:46:32.361 --> 00:46:34.887
Hi, hi.

00:46:41.148 --> 00:46:43.497
What's that?

00:46:43.497 --> 00:46:46.208
It's our two-year anniversary today,

00:46:46.208 --> 00:46:49.086
and the dog daycare is closed.

00:46:49.086 --> 00:46:52.323
Coco's super friendly and fully house-trained.

00:46:52.323 --> 00:46:54.508
She's no trouble at all.

00:46:54.508 --> 00:46:58.120
Just give her some love
and a treat now and then.

00:47:00.143 --> 00:47:01.805
If you're busy, I can ask someone else...

00:47:01.805 --> 00:47:05.055
No, I'll watch her. Go have fun.

00:47:06.220 --> 00:47:08.647
- I'm off.
- All right, bye.

00:47:08.647 --> 00:47:10.941
Mom's leaving, Coco.

00:47:10.941 --> 00:47:13.343
Bye-bye.

00:47:15.863 --> 00:47:18.936
Okay, secured one dog sitter.

00:47:20.368 --> 00:47:23.263
[Spring]
My whole family's out of town, so...

00:47:23.263 --> 00:47:25.075
Yeah, go enjoy yourself.

00:47:25.075 --> 00:47:26.097
Hey.

00:47:26.097 --> 00:47:27.616
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

00:47:27.616 --> 00:47:28.744
[Summer]

00:47:28.744 --> 00:47:30.305
Hey.

00:47:30.305 --> 00:47:31.763
I'm on summer vacation starting tomorrow.

00:47:31.763 --> 00:47:33.222
Yeah, have fun.

00:47:33.222 --> 00:47:35.391
Coco, come here.

00:47:35.391 --> 00:47:36.759
[Fall]

00:47:36.759 --> 00:47:39.350
We're going to Gangneung.

00:47:39.350 --> 00:47:40.721
Have fun.

00:47:40.721 --> 00:47:42.415
- Bye.
- Safe trip!

00:47:42.415 --> 00:47:44.016
Just as Ruby planned,

00:47:44.016 --> 00:47:46.756
Yumi became Coco's sitter.

00:47:54.311 --> 00:47:57.013
[Winter]
Coco, look at this.

00:47:57.013 --> 00:47:58.823
It's a little jacket.

00:47:58.823 --> 00:48:00.825
Writer Kim, how about this one?

00:48:00.825 --> 00:48:03.156
I'm going with bunny.

00:48:03.893 --> 00:48:05.365
Pick the one you like.

00:48:07.587 --> 00:48:09.388
See that?

00:48:09.388 --> 00:48:10.892
So cute.

00:48:10.892 --> 00:48:12.626
Coco.

00:48:12.626 --> 00:48:14.046
Look at this.

00:48:14.046 --> 00:48:15.805
Lovely.

00:48:15.805 --> 00:48:19.222
"Mom, I'm doing great."

00:48:24.305 --> 00:48:28.270
[Spring again]
That was a big one. Yeah?

00:48:29.885 --> 00:48:30.938
And so,

00:48:30.938 --> 00:48:34.574
on days the Maltese comes by...

00:48:36.846 --> 00:48:40.281
Did you sleep well? Here you go.

00:48:40.281 --> 00:48:42.376
Your fur looks a bit rough.

00:48:42.376 --> 00:48:46.209
I'll brush it nice and pretty.

00:48:46.209 --> 00:48:47.222
Oh, that scent.

00:48:47.222 --> 00:48:49.914
So golden and thick.

00:48:49.914 --> 00:48:52.993
The whole village is buzzing again.

00:48:52.993 --> 00:48:55.773
Hey, your paws are so tiny.

00:49:01.853 --> 00:49:03.761
Why isn't she here yet?

00:49:03.761 --> 00:49:06.238
I told her to come early.

00:49:06.238 --> 00:49:08.557
Right, Coco?

00:49:08.557 --> 00:49:11.663
Oh, that must be her.

00:49:12.954 --> 00:49:16.607
The only problem with dog mom Yumi is...

00:49:17.244 --> 00:49:19.737
this person.

00:49:26.701 --> 00:49:29.161
Hello, it's Shin Soon Rok.

00:49:29.161 --> 00:49:31.521
Hold on.

00:49:37.545 --> 00:49:40.089
- Hello?
- Na Hui.

00:49:40.089 --> 00:49:41.263
I told you to come early.

00:49:41.263 --> 00:49:43.384
PD Shin's here. Where are you?

00:49:43.384 --> 00:49:47.388
I got a taxi, but the tire blew out.

00:49:47.388 --> 00:49:49.373
- What?
- They're changing it now.

00:49:49.373 --> 00:49:53.126
I'll be a bit late. Sorry.

00:49:53.126 --> 00:49:56.399
Okay. Be careful.

00:49:59.567 --> 00:50:02.119
This is bad, Coco.

00:50:02.842 --> 00:50:06.388
You think you can turn on the charm?

00:50:29.805 --> 00:50:32.475
- Hello.
- Hello.

00:50:32.475 --> 00:50:35.252
Sorry I'm a bit late...

00:50:36.437 --> 00:50:39.001
Coco, no barking.

00:50:41.472 --> 00:50:44.612
Oh, do you have a dog?

00:50:44.612 --> 00:50:45.821
No.

00:50:45.821 --> 00:50:48.599
She belongs to a close friend.
I watch her sometimes.

00:50:48.599 --> 00:50:50.493
They're on vacation right now.

00:50:50.493 --> 00:50:52.834
- Come in.
- Okay.

00:50:52.834 --> 00:50:55.829
Coco, quiet.

00:50:55.829 --> 00:50:58.084
She's gentle,

00:50:58.084 --> 00:51:00.430
just a little timid.

00:51:00.430 --> 00:51:01.928
Come in.

00:51:01.928 --> 00:51:03.339
Sure.

00:51:03.339 --> 00:51:05.299
By any chance...

00:51:05.299 --> 00:51:07.635
Do you not like dogs?

00:51:07.635 --> 00:51:11.872
Or are you scared of them?
Or allergies or anything...

00:51:11.872 --> 00:51:13.315
No, not really.

00:51:13.315 --> 00:51:16.310
Oh, that's a relief.

00:51:16.310 --> 00:51:20.023
Then could you pet her?

00:51:21.305 --> 00:51:23.779
You want me to?

00:51:23.779 --> 00:51:26.946
Yeah, she warms up faster if you do.

00:51:26.946 --> 00:51:29.546
She might keep barking.

00:51:32.084 --> 00:51:34.317
Okay.

00:51:40.358 --> 00:51:42.516
See? She likes you.

00:51:42.516 --> 00:51:43.754
Does she?

00:51:43.754 --> 00:51:45.047
Of course.

00:51:45.047 --> 00:51:47.381
You like him, right?

00:51:47.381 --> 00:51:48.654
What would you like to drink?

00:51:48.654 --> 00:51:51.439
I have coffee, or orange juice.

00:51:51.439 --> 00:51:53.317
I'll take juice, please.

00:51:53.317 --> 00:51:54.347
Sure.

00:51:54.347 --> 00:51:56.888
Stay still.

00:52:01.555 --> 00:52:03.301
That's a relief.

00:52:03.301 --> 00:52:06.193
At least it started naturally
thanks to the Maltese.

00:52:06.193 --> 00:52:08.429
Why does Yumi have to try this hard?

00:52:08.429 --> 00:52:09.597
What's his deal?

00:52:09.597 --> 00:52:11.680
Exactly!

00:52:11.680 --> 00:52:14.180
What a jerk.

00:52:17.420 --> 00:52:20.306
The weather's nice, right?

00:52:21.375 --> 00:52:23.401
It is.

00:52:24.057 --> 00:52:26.830
Did you have a good weekend?

00:52:26.830 --> 00:52:28.956
Yeah.

00:52:31.189 --> 00:52:33.329
Why don't you ask her too?

00:52:33.329 --> 00:52:35.273
If she had a good weekend?

00:52:35.273 --> 00:52:37.892
That's basic social skills, Shin Soon Rok!

00:52:37.892 --> 00:52:40.305
This isn't your first time
interacting with people, is it?

00:52:40.305 --> 00:52:42.388
Let go!

00:52:49.673 --> 00:52:51.648
Did you

00:52:51.648 --> 00:52:54.366
have a good weekend too?

00:52:54.366 --> 00:52:57.090
Yeah.

00:52:57.090 --> 00:52:58.558
That's better.

00:52:58.558 --> 00:53:00.891
That's how you do it.

00:53:00.891 --> 00:53:03.582
I spent the weekend with Coco.

00:53:03.582 --> 00:53:06.013
I watch her about once a month,

00:53:06.013 --> 00:53:08.374
and we go to this dog cafe.

00:53:08.374 --> 00:53:11.872
I meet a friend there who has a dog too.

00:53:11.872 --> 00:53:13.222
I see.

00:53:13.222 --> 00:53:16.597
When I let her run on the grass,
she runs like crazy.

00:53:16.597 --> 00:53:18.837
She's not even mine,

00:53:18.837 --> 00:53:21.034
but she's just so cute.

00:53:21.034 --> 00:53:25.400
I swear she was born just to be cute.

00:53:26.972 --> 00:53:30.013
Isn't she just a Maltese?

00:53:30.013 --> 00:53:31.049
What?

00:53:31.049 --> 00:53:34.255
She looks like a typical Maltese.

00:53:39.112 --> 00:53:42.373
Right. Just a typical Maltese.

00:53:43.414 --> 00:53:46.542
I mean, Maltese are cute.

00:53:46.542 --> 00:53:49.302
Oh, yeah.

00:53:55.110 --> 00:53:56.927
I hate him.

00:53:56.927 --> 00:53:59.764
I really hate Shin Soon Rok.

00:53:59.764 --> 00:54:01.515
Seriously.

00:54:01.515 --> 00:54:06.175
It's been a while
since I've hated someone this much.

00:54:11.942 --> 00:54:14.188
Thank you.

00:54:20.931 --> 00:54:22.912
Another silence.

00:54:22.912 --> 00:54:25.081
We're back in silence again.

00:54:25.081 --> 00:54:27.792
Hey, stop trying so hard.

00:54:27.792 --> 00:54:29.960
Yumi did her best.

00:54:29.960 --> 00:54:33.240
The problem is that jerk.

00:54:40.262 --> 00:54:42.531
Oh, she's here.

00:54:44.428 --> 00:54:46.538
- Hello.
- Oh, PD Jang.

00:54:46.538 --> 00:54:49.618
I ran into her right outside. Sorry I'm late.

00:54:49.618 --> 00:54:51.899
Come in. PD Shin is already here.

00:54:51.899 --> 00:54:53.917
Hello.

00:54:53.917 --> 00:54:55.764
Hello.

00:54:55.764 --> 00:54:57.763
Oh my gosh, what is this?

00:54:57.763 --> 00:54:58.805
Is that a Maltese?

00:54:58.805 --> 00:55:00.616
Oh, so cute!

00:55:00.616 --> 00:55:02.729
Her name is Coco. Isn't she adorable?

00:55:02.729 --> 00:55:05.079
She's so cute. Oh my goodness.

00:55:05.079 --> 00:55:07.771
- Coco, Coco.
- PD Jang,

00:55:07.771 --> 00:55:09.900
what would you like to drink?
I was just about to make coffee.

00:55:09.900 --> 00:55:12.319
Coffee for me, of course.

00:55:12.319 --> 00:55:14.305
What kind of coffee do you have?

00:55:14.305 --> 00:55:17.717
I've got three capsules. Come pick one.

00:55:17.717 --> 00:55:20.097
Thank god. The mood finally loosened up.

00:55:20.097 --> 00:55:22.112
That's a relief.

00:55:22.112 --> 00:55:23.889
This isn't something to celebrate.

00:55:23.889 --> 00:55:25.624
Why are we grateful for this?

00:55:25.624 --> 00:55:28.436
Hey, aren't you sleepy?

00:55:28.436 --> 00:55:30.766
We're about to start the meeting.
You can go sleep if you want.

00:55:30.766 --> 00:55:31.805
I'm not sleeping.

00:55:31.805 --> 00:55:35.513
I'm watching this till the end.

00:55:42.724 --> 00:55:45.149
I really liked this part.

00:55:45.149 --> 00:55:47.714
It feels very... stylish.

00:55:47.714 --> 00:55:49.865
This is definitely going to hit.

00:55:49.865 --> 00:55:51.428
Really?

00:55:51.428 --> 00:55:54.587
I liked it too. That part gave me butterflies.

00:55:54.587 --> 00:55:56.465
Right? Same here.

00:55:56.465 --> 00:55:58.013
It really got my heart racing.

00:55:58.013 --> 00:56:01.722
I thought it might not work,
so that's a relief.

00:56:04.456 --> 00:56:06.033
PD Shin,

00:56:06.033 --> 00:56:08.786
any thoughts?

00:56:13.426 --> 00:56:15.106
It's good.

00:56:15.106 --> 00:56:16.149
Oh, really?

00:56:16.149 --> 00:56:19.095
Yeah, I enjoyed it.

00:56:19.095 --> 00:56:21.529
There's just one thing, though.

00:56:21.529 --> 00:56:23.609
What is it?

00:56:24.908 --> 00:56:27.642
About the Maltese the male lead has...

00:56:27.642 --> 00:56:31.777
I think we should change the breed.

00:56:31.777 --> 00:56:32.805
Why?

00:56:32.805 --> 00:56:35.469
The dog is supposed to be very intelligent.

00:56:35.469 --> 00:56:36.502
Yes?

00:56:36.502 --> 00:56:38.087
But Maltese

00:56:38.087 --> 00:56:40.641
aren't that smart.

00:56:41.257 --> 00:56:43.034
Maltese aren't smart?

00:56:43.034 --> 00:56:44.344
I thought they were.

00:56:44.344 --> 00:56:45.511
Not particularly.

00:56:45.511 --> 00:56:49.599
Isn't the smart one a Border Collie?

00:56:49.599 --> 00:56:52.171
Maltese

00:56:52.171 --> 00:56:54.484
are smart.

00:56:56.680 --> 00:56:59.650
When I'm feeling down,
she stays quietly by my side,

00:56:59.650 --> 00:57:02.737
and when I'm happy,
she somehow knows and brings me a ball.

00:57:02.737 --> 00:57:05.138
She even recognizes her owner
on video calls and barks.

00:57:05.138 --> 00:57:06.597
She's really smart.

00:57:06.597 --> 00:57:08.951
Don't all dogs do that?

00:57:08.951 --> 00:57:11.504
Unless it's a lizard.

00:57:14.798 --> 00:57:16.292
Well, that's true.

00:57:16.292 --> 00:57:19.347
Even my grandma's mixed-breed dog
does all that.

00:57:19.347 --> 00:57:21.547
That's not the same.

00:57:21.547 --> 00:57:23.508
I don't raise one myself,

00:57:23.508 --> 00:57:25.868
but I do know a thing or two about dogs.

00:57:25.868 --> 00:57:28.346
Have you read this, by any chance?

00:57:28.346 --> 00:57:31.057
According to Stanley Coren's
dog intelligence rankings,

00:57:31.057 --> 00:57:35.815
out of 79 breeds, Maltese rank 59th.

00:57:35.815 --> 00:57:37.046
[Maltese: 59th]
59th?

00:57:37.046 --> 00:57:38.097
Seriously?

00:57:38.097 --> 00:57:39.956
Why are Maltese so dumb?

00:57:39.956 --> 00:57:42.110
If it's officially ranked, it must be true.

00:57:42.110 --> 00:57:44.195
That's just statistics.

00:57:44.195 --> 00:57:46.353
It's different when you actually raise one.

00:57:46.353 --> 00:57:48.391
She understands human emotions.

00:57:48.391 --> 00:57:50.882
Emotional response
and intelligence are different.

00:57:50.882 --> 00:57:53.847
Here's another reference.

00:57:53.847 --> 00:57:57.555
"Intelligence is measured by
problem-solving ability and trainability."

00:57:57.555 --> 00:57:59.735
So what you mentioned, empathy,

00:57:59.735 --> 00:58:02.370
has nothing to do with it.

00:58:06.638 --> 00:58:08.761
So...

00:58:08.761 --> 00:58:10.555
what you're saying is...

00:58:10.555 --> 00:58:12.273
The dog in your story

00:58:12.273 --> 00:58:14.475
is basically at genius level.

00:58:14.475 --> 00:58:16.406
For that level of performance,

00:58:16.406 --> 00:58:19.313
it should be a smarter breed.

00:58:19.313 --> 00:58:21.740
That makes sense.

00:58:24.293 --> 00:58:26.472
Shin Soon Rok.

00:58:26.472 --> 00:58:28.771
You're pretty thorough.

00:58:28.771 --> 00:58:31.632
Okay, then maybe we should change it
to a Border Collie...

00:58:31.632 --> 00:58:33.493
Hey, stop!

00:58:33.493 --> 00:58:34.954
Hey, Writer Cell!

00:58:34.954 --> 00:58:37.879
You're really going to accept that
without any pride?

00:58:37.879 --> 00:58:39.917
Fact-checking matters.

00:58:39.917 --> 00:58:41.763
If it's a fact that Maltese are dumb,

00:58:41.763 --> 00:58:45.606
- then it's better to...
- What "fact" are you talking about?

00:58:45.606 --> 00:58:47.089
Even if it were a fact,

00:58:47.089 --> 00:58:50.383
you can't just agree to that.

00:58:50.383 --> 00:58:54.265
He's saying that right in front of a Maltese.

00:58:54.265 --> 00:58:58.078
That's straight-up discrimination.

00:58:58.078 --> 00:59:00.713
Breed discrimination, technically.

00:59:00.713 --> 00:59:02.853
- You don't even know...
- Whatever!

00:59:02.853 --> 00:59:04.880
Coco's feelings are hurt.

00:59:04.880 --> 00:59:06.777
How would a dog even understand that?

00:59:06.777 --> 00:59:08.427
She understands everything.

00:59:08.427 --> 00:59:10.400
Dogs can tell just from your tone

00:59:10.400 --> 00:59:13.779
whether it's praise or an insult.

00:59:16.641 --> 00:59:18.533
That jerk

00:59:18.533 --> 00:59:23.153
has the nerve to insult
Maltese owners everywhere?

00:59:26.720 --> 00:59:28.076
But...

00:59:28.076 --> 00:59:30.468
Border Collies are kind of big.

00:59:30.468 --> 00:59:34.079
I think a small dog fits the male lead better.

00:59:34.079 --> 00:59:35.598
Then how about a poodle?

00:59:35.598 --> 00:59:38.984
Right, poodles are supposed to
be really smart too.

00:59:38.984 --> 00:59:40.860
PD Shin,

00:59:40.860 --> 00:59:42.460
you know what?

00:59:42.460 --> 00:59:44.680
At the 2022 World Dog Master Classic in Brazil,

00:59:44.680 --> 00:59:47.864
second place went to

00:59:47.864 --> 00:59:50.004
a Maltese named Lucas.

00:59:50.004 --> 00:59:52.375
Oh, for real?

00:59:52.375 --> 00:59:53.980
"Dog Master Classic?"

00:59:53.980 --> 00:59:56.791
Out of 300 purebred dogs,

00:59:56.791 --> 00:59:58.495
it took second place.

00:59:58.495 --> 01:00:02.750
Which means intelligence can vary
depending on training.

01:00:02.750 --> 01:00:06.187
So the idea of fixed,
innate intelligence is flawed.

01:00:06.187 --> 01:00:08.105
So Maltese can be smart.

01:00:08.105 --> 01:00:10.516
There's no such thing as a dumb dog.

01:00:10.516 --> 01:00:12.203
It depends on the owner.

01:00:12.203 --> 01:00:13.222
Do you still think

01:00:13.222 --> 01:00:16.470
it's common knowledge that Maltese are dumb?

01:00:16.470 --> 01:00:18.793
I don't think so.

01:00:18.793 --> 01:00:21.384
That was just my opinion.

01:00:21.384 --> 01:00:24.654
It's not a major issue for the story.

01:00:24.654 --> 01:00:27.014
Then let's just keep it as a Maltese.

01:00:27.014 --> 01:00:31.090
Maltese is good. Cute and smart.

01:00:31.090 --> 01:00:33.058
Okay.

01:00:40.119 --> 01:00:42.855
Look at him back down.

01:00:42.855 --> 01:00:45.166
Facts shut him right up.

01:00:45.166 --> 01:00:47.168
But was that actually real?

01:00:47.168 --> 01:00:48.836
That Dog Master Classic?

01:00:48.836 --> 01:00:50.569
I've never heard of it.

01:00:50.569 --> 01:00:51.641
Whatever.

01:00:51.641 --> 01:00:55.001
He shut up, that's what matters.

01:00:55.001 --> 01:00:57.747
Wait, you made that up?

01:01:05.118 --> 01:01:07.162
Going down.

01:01:07.162 --> 01:01:08.397
Good work.

01:01:08.397 --> 01:01:11.788
- Good job today.
- Let's keep it up.

01:01:12.563 --> 01:01:15.127
- Bye, Coco.
- See you, Coco.

01:01:15.127 --> 01:01:17.540
Take care.

01:01:17.540 --> 01:01:18.817
Coco, paw.

01:01:18.817 --> 01:01:21.250
Good girl.

01:01:21.250 --> 01:01:23.579
You're smart.

01:01:23.579 --> 01:01:25.915
See how smart she is?

01:01:25.915 --> 01:01:28.751
And he wants to replace her
because she's "not smart?"

01:01:28.751 --> 01:01:31.337
Is that even supposed to make sense?

01:01:31.337 --> 01:01:34.643
You agree, right?

01:01:34.643 --> 01:01:36.516
[PD Shin Soon Rok]

01:01:36.516 --> 01:01:38.552
Huh?

01:01:38.552 --> 01:01:41.025
Coco, hold on.

01:01:46.180 --> 01:01:48.014
Hello?

01:01:48.014 --> 01:01:49.105
Writer Kim,

01:01:49.105 --> 01:01:51.763
I think I left my document envelope there.

01:01:51.763 --> 01:01:54.722
The envelope? One second.

01:01:56.347 --> 01:01:58.773
Yes, it's here.

01:01:58.773 --> 01:02:00.633
That's a relief.

01:02:00.633 --> 01:02:02.910
Would it be okay if I stop by tomorrow?

01:02:02.910 --> 01:02:04.854
I can come around five.

01:02:04.854 --> 01:02:08.207
Sure, anytime. I'll be here.

01:02:08.207 --> 01:02:09.452
Thank you.

01:02:09.452 --> 01:02:10.878
Yeah.

01:02:10.878 --> 01:02:12.303
Oh, right.

01:02:12.303 --> 01:02:13.741
Also...

01:02:13.741 --> 01:02:17.792
That Brazil Dog Master Classic
you mentioned earlier.

01:02:17.792 --> 01:02:20.624
What exactly is that?

01:02:20.624 --> 01:02:22.813
I couldn't find the results anywhere.

01:02:22.813 --> 01:02:24.938
[2022 Brazil Dog Master Classic]

01:02:29.460 --> 01:02:33.011
Oh, you couldn't find it?

01:02:33.011 --> 01:02:36.198
I read about it in an English article.

01:02:37.859 --> 01:02:40.760
Could you send me the link?

01:02:42.045 --> 01:02:44.602
So he's calm and rational, huh...

01:02:44.602 --> 01:02:45.638
Guess that's true.

01:02:45.638 --> 01:02:48.680
Annoyingly calm. Annoyingly rational.

01:02:48.680 --> 01:02:50.629
Why does he nitpick everything?

01:02:50.629 --> 01:02:53.389
That's why you shouldn't lie.

01:02:55.712 --> 01:02:57.047
The link?

01:02:57.047 --> 01:02:58.945
Yes, I'm just curious.

01:02:58.945 --> 01:03:02.135
A Maltese placed second
in a world competition that's interesting.

01:03:02.135 --> 01:03:04.121
What's so surprising about that?

01:03:04.121 --> 01:03:06.723
Maltese can be smart too.

01:03:06.723 --> 01:03:07.932
The Maltese I know...

01:03:07.932 --> 01:03:11.305
What do you even know about Maltese?

01:03:13.605 --> 01:03:15.525
Maltese...

01:03:16.352 --> 01:03:18.785
Don't they eat poop?

01:03:20.195 --> 01:03:22.539
[Poop]

01:03:25.576 --> 01:03:27.716
At that moment,

01:03:27.716 --> 01:03:29.412
another cell

01:03:29.412 --> 01:03:32.298
awoke from a long slumber.

01:03:34.149 --> 01:03:35.900
Did you just say

01:03:35.900 --> 01:03:37.718
a poop-eating dog?

01:03:37.718 --> 01:03:39.595
This is just my personal opinion,

01:03:39.595 --> 01:03:41.277
but Maltese...

01:03:41.277 --> 01:03:43.035
Oh, taxi's here. Sorry.

01:03:43.035 --> 01:03:45.410
I'll come by tomorrow.

01:03:46.596 --> 01:03:49.690
Hello? Hello?

01:03:51.670 --> 01:03:53.144
Coco, don't listen.

01:03:53.144 --> 01:03:55.717
Just forget it.

01:03:59.638 --> 01:04:02.713
Damn, I feel wide awake
for the first time in a while.

01:04:02.713 --> 01:04:04.614
These stairs are brutal. Shit.

01:04:04.614 --> 01:04:07.809
What was that? Our Maltese eats poop?

01:04:07.809 --> 01:04:09.878
What kind of bullshit is that?

01:04:09.878 --> 01:04:12.740
How about you shut that damn mouth of yours?

01:04:12.740 --> 01:04:16.193
Why don't you eat it yourself, you asshole?

01:04:46.290 --> 01:04:48.975
How does he take all eight
for himself like that?

01:04:48.975 --> 01:04:52.253
This place never gets a moment of peace!

01:04:52.253 --> 01:04:54.898
I'll take everything you've got.

01:04:54.898 --> 01:04:56.124
Shin Soon Rok.

01:04:56.124 --> 01:04:59.001
I've got you completely figured out.

01:04:59.001 --> 01:05:00.013
PD Shin.

01:05:00.013 --> 01:05:02.128
Shin Soon Rok? What now?

01:05:02.128 --> 01:05:03.363
Watch out!

01:05:03.363 --> 01:05:05.795
How long have you been driving?

01:05:05.795 --> 01:05:09.130
She's totally lost it!

01:05:09.130 --> 01:05:10.472
Don't come. please.

01:05:10.472 --> 01:05:12.690
Writer Kim?